reviews.text:
The Baked Potato pizza is sinfully delicious! But you honestly can't go wrong with any of the options.

Great service, chill vibes, and TVs for entertainment (the Savannah Bananas were playing when we were there).

We ordered two slices to have at the restaurant and one pie to-go. The slices tasted good, but they were still cool when we got them, the cheese was still firm on them, not soft and melted. The take home pizza, however, was very good. We ordered a meatball with ricotta and all of the flavors were on point.

Extremely nice service, pizza came out fast and was perfection. Just came from Brooklyn/Manhattan NYC yesterday and was already craving some of the many pizzas we had there. This is fantastic NY style. 10/10 - will come back!

Please read entirely as it contains edits post the owner's response.
Initial review: They put bacon in my pizza instead of basil! I'm a vegetarian, and this is outrageous. Never returning back here again. Definitely not one of the top rated places in my mind, despite what Google would suggest.

Writing post the owner's response: they don't seem to understand that I cannot eat meat for religious reasons, and casually indicate that they put bacon instead of basil because the buttons are next to each other. I would not have given a bad review if the basil was accidentally replaced with another veggie or cheese. I can understand that mistakes happen.
However, instead of fixing their ordering system to separate meats and veggies (like many other pizza places do), the owner responds to me in a sarcastic way to indicate that I was rude during my initial review.

I have literally never written a review for a place but I was so impressed. I am from the north east both my parents from NYC I grew up in NJ and PA take out pizza was a staple. I have lived in Lincoln for over a year now and I‚Äôve been looking for pizza that is like what I grew up eating. This is literally as close to my favorite pizza in New York or the north east as you could get in Lincoln as far as I can tell. The sauce really brought me back the crust was a great texture not too crispy but perfectly cooked on the bottom. I went and got two slices and enjoyed it so much that I ordered a whole pie to go. When I got home I tried my pizza and it was everything I hoped for. If you are from the north east or you want to see what it is like definitely get pizza here. I recommend getting a fresh made to order pie as nothing will be as good as that but the slices were still pretty good.
